{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:ephesians.3",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "ephesians",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Ephesians 3 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:1",
      "text": "For this cause, I Paul, the prisoner of Jesus Christ, for you Gentiles:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:2",
      "text": "If yet you have heard of the dispensation of the grace of God which is given me towards you:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:3",
      "text": "How that, according to revelation, the mystery has been made known to me, as I have written above in a few words:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:4",
      "text": "As you reading, may understand my knowledge in the mystery of Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:5",
      "text": "Which in other generations was not known to the sons of men, as it is now revealed to his holy apostles and prophets in the Spirit:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:6",
      "text": "That the Gentiles should be fellow heirs and of the same body: and copartners of his promise in Christ Jesus, by the gospel",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:7",
      "text": "Of which I am made a minister, according to the gift of the grace of God, which is given to me according to the operation of his power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:8",
      "text": "To me, the least of all the saints, is given this grace, to preach among the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:9",
      "text": "And to enlighten all men, that they may see what is the dispensation of the mystery which hath been hidden from eternity in God who created all things:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:10",
      "text": "That the manifold wisdom of God may be made known to the principalities and powers in heavenly places through the church,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:11",
      "text": "According to the eternal purpose which he made in Christ Jesus our Lord:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:12",
      "text": "In whom we have boldness and access with confidence by the faith of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:13",
      "text": "Wherefore I pray you not to faint at my tribulations for you, which is your glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:14",
      "text": "For this cause I bow my knees to the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:15",
      "text": "Of whom all paternity in heaven and earth is named:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:16",
      "text": "That he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, to be strengthened by his Spirit with might unto the inward man:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:17",
      "text": "That Christ may dwell by faith in your hearts: that, being rooted and founded in charity,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:18",
      "text": "You may be able to comprehend, with all the saints, what is the breadth and length and height and depth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:19",
      "text": "To know also the charity of Christ, which surpasseth all knowledge: that you may be filled unto all the fulness of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:20",
      "text": "Now to him who is able to do all things more abundantly than we desire or understand, according to the power that worketh in us:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:ephesians.3.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 3:21",
      "text": "To him be glory in the church and in Christ Jesus, unto all generations, world without end. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
